<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-02T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-02T22:00:00-05:00" n="135" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d135">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5855: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan (<persName type="from">Grew</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-03T12:00:00+09:00">February 3,
                                1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 3—12:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>34. Peiping’s 79 and 80 just received by mail.<note n="67" xml:id="d135fn67">No. 79, dated January 23, 7 p.m., not printed; No.
                                80, dated January 24, 11 a.m., is printed on <ref target="#pg_124">p. 124</ref>.</note> Guarded remarks of Japanese General Staff
                            officers here to Military Attaché yesterday indicate that Japanese Army
                            hopes to reach arrangement regarding Jehol by negotiations of some
                            kind.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>